# lean-ctx — Context Engineering Layer

<!-- lean-ctx-rules-v12 -->

## Mode: Hybrid (MCP reads + CLI shell)

**CRITICAL:** Native `Read`, `Grep`, `Glob`, and raw `Shell` are **forbidden** when lean-ctx MCP is available. Use `ctx_read` with an explicit read mode. Hooks in `~/.cursor/hooks.json` redirect `Read|Grep|Glob` → lean-ctx.

## Tool Mapping (MANDATORY)

| Instead of                   | MUST USE                             | Example                           |
| ---------------------------- | ------------------------------------ | --------------------------------- |
| Read/cat/head/tail           | `ctx_read(path, mode)`               | `ctx_read("src/main.rs", "full")` |
| Grep/rg/find                 | `ctx_search(pattern, path)`          | `ctx_search("fn handle", "src/")` |
| Shell/bash                   | `lean-ctx -c "<cmd>"` or `ctx_shell` | `lean-ctx -c "yarn test"`         |
| ls/find tree                 | `ctx_tree(path, depth)`              | `ctx_tree("src", 3)`              |
| Edit (when Read unavailable) | `ctx_edit(path, old, new)`           | `ctx_edit("f.rs", "old", "new")`  |

Native `Edit` / `Write` / `StrReplace` remain allowed for writes after `ctx_read(..., "full")`.

## ctx_read — pick a mode (never omit mode on purpose)

Docs: [Read Modes](https://leanctx.com/docs/concepts/read-modes/)

| Goal                   | Mode         | Notes                              |
| ---------------------- | ------------ | ---------------------------------- |
| Will edit this file    | `full`       | First read before any edit         |
| After edit             | `diff`       | ~13 tok on unchanged re-read       |
| API / exports only     | `signatures` | ~87% savings                       |
| File role / deps       | `map`        | ~85–95% savings                    |
| Large boilerplate file | `entropy`    | Shannon-filtered                   |
| Verbose comments       | `aggressive` | Strips comments/whitespace         |
| Task-scoped slice      | `task`       | Requires `ctx_session` task set    |
| Pointer only           | `reference`  | ~1 line, no body                   |
| Known line range       | `lines:N-M`  | Surgical (e.g. `lines:42-80`)      |
| Unsure                 | `auto`       | lean-ctx picks; use when exploring |

**Decision:** edit → `full`; re-read → `diff`; orient → `map`/`signatures`; unsure → `auto`.

## Workflow: Orient → Locate → Read → Edit → Verify → Record

1. `ctx_overview(task)` or `ctx_compose(task)` — orient
2. `ctx_search` / `ctx_semantic_search` — locate
3. `ctx_read(path, mode)` — read with correct mode
4. Native Edit / `ctx_edit` — write
5. `ctx_read(path, "diff")` + `lean-ctx -c "verify cmd"` — verify
6. `ctx_knowledge(action="remember")` — record non-obvious facts

Session start: `ctx_session(action="load")` + `ctx_knowledge(action="wakeup")`.

REMINDER: NEVER use native Read, Grep, Glob, or Shell when ctx\_\* / lean-ctx equivalents exist.

